========================================================================
Section 1: Source of Delta_DS^(4) = 23.796910
========================================================================

  There is NO standalone source file delta_E4.py or m8a_source.py.
  The value 23.796910 originates from the LaTeX paper section
  'The Exceptional Prime Set for pi/10' and appears as a
  sub-identity 'm8a_identity' inside:
    certificates/m23_bsd_j0_143.py  (Module 23: BSD for J_0(143))

  The m8a_identity in M23 computes:
    Delta_DS / H4_base = 23.79691 / 10.90909 = 2.1812
    Compare: 2*(12/11) = 2.1818  =>  match within 0.027%

  This identity uses the PRE-AUDIT paper value.
  Module 15 (certified 2026-05-23) supersedes it.

========================================================================
Section 2: Errors Found in LaTeX Paper (M15 Audit)
========================================================================

  E1: All 16 ||p*pi/10|| table values in LaTeX paper are wrong (errors 1.79e-5 to 3.76e-1)
  E2: Sign error: paper computes -log(||.||) + log(p) but definition says -log(||.||) - log(p)
  E3: Delta_DS^(4) = 23.796910 follows from E1+E2 compounding; correct value = 2.753126094323295
  E4: p_5 > 6*10^12 claim is wrong; certified p_5 = 3993746143633 < 6*10^12

========================================================================
Section 3: Certified Correct Values (from M15, SHA cf1620c7...)
========================================================================

  Formula: delta_p = -log(||p*pi/10||) - log(p)  [natural log]
  Precision: mpmath 100 dps

  ||p*pi/10|| certified values:
    ||  2*pi/10|| = 0.37168146928204135231
    ||  3*pi/10|| = 0.057522203923062028461
    || 19*pi/10|| = 0.030973958179392846921
    ||191*pi/10|| = 0.0044196835650508546365

  delta_p certified values:
    delta_  2 = 0.29657087632449742694
    delta_  3 = 1.756971961865759705
    delta_ 19 = 0.5301695071068816828
    delta_191 = 0.16941374902615628599

  TRUE  Delta_DS^(4) = SUM(delta_p) = 2.753126094323295100690126
  PAPER Delta_DS^(4)                = 23.796910
  Difference                        = 21.043784  (paper off by factor ~8.6x)

